w Zealand, and the United States. So Rahe asserts, and he explains what must be done to reverse this unfortunate trend.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aDemocracy. 0aRepublicanism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300156102423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300156102.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles